<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" author="Clemencon, H" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="21 - 27" refId="B7" refString="Clemencon, H, Hongo, T, 1994. Notes on three Japanese Agaricales. Mycoscience 35: 21 - 27, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" title="Notes on three Japanese Agaricales." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" volume="35" year="1994">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Clémençon">Clemencon</normalizedToken>
and Hongo (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
originally published this taxon as 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Alnicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alnicola lactariolens" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lactariolens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Alnicola lactariolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the April issue of Mycoscience, apparently published on 1 Apr 1994; it appears Corner had effectively published the paper including the same taxon one day earlier, on 31 Mar 1994 as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corner" authorityYear="1993" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Psathyrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Psathyrella verrucispora" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="verrucispora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Psathyrella verrucispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both are morphologically clearly members of 
<taxonomicName authority="Porphyrospora" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma subsp. section" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Porphyrospora" species="verrucispora" subSpecies="section">Hebeloma section Porphyrospora</taxonomicName>
. The authors of both papers comment on the purple-brown (vinaceous) spore print, 
<bibRefCitation author="Corner, EJH" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" publicationUrl="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" refId="B8" refString="Corner, EJH, 1994 [&quot;1993&quot;]. Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337-357. https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" title="Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337 - 357." url="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" year="1994 [&quot; 1993 &quot;]">
Corner (1994 [
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1993”">&quot;1993&quot;</normalizedToken>
]
</bibRefCitation>
, p. 345) notes that the spore deposit color is fuscous purple, which is why he described his species in 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Psathyrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Psathyrella" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Psathyrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Lacrymaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lacrymaria" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Lacrymaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" author="Clemencon, H" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="21 - 27" refId="B7" refString="Clemencon, H, Hongo, T, 1994. Notes on three Japanese Agaricales. Mycoscience 35: 21 - 27, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" title="Notes on three Japanese Agaricales." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" volume="35" year="1994">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Clémençon">Clemencon</normalizedToken>
and Hongo (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
commented on the spore deposit being a dark purple-brown color, an unknown feature of 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Alnicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alnicola" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Alnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756205003758" author="Yang, ZL" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="1259 - 1267" refId="B55" refString="Yang, ZL, Matheny, PB, Ge, Z-W, Slot, JC, Hibbett, DS, 2005. New Asian species of the genus Anamika (Euagarics, hebelomatoid Clade) based on morphology and ribosomal DNA sequences. Mycological Research 109: 1259 - 1267, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756205003758" title="New Asian species of the genus Anamika (Euagarics, hebelomatoid Clade) based on morphology and ribosomal DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756205003758" volume="109" year="2005">Yang et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Alnicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alnicola lactariolens" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lactariolens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Alnicola lactariolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recombined into 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Anamika" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Anamika" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Anamika</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and later by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/12-404" author="Rees, BJ" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="1043 - 1058" refId="B36" refString="Rees, BJ, Midgley, DJ, Marchant, A, Lerkins, A, Orlovich, DA, 2013. Morphological and molecular data for Australian Hebeloma species do not support the generic status of Anamika. Mycologia 105: 1043 - 1058, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/12-404" title="Morphological and molecular data for Australian Hebeloma species do not support the generic status of Anamika." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/12-404" volume="105" year="2013">Rees et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
into 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Hebeloma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The spore deposit color and its typical color change upon storage is the most striking feature of members of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. subsp. sect." order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Porphyrospora" species="lactariolens" subSpecies="sect.">H. sect. Porphyrospora</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2019.1680220" author="Eberhardt, U" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="172 - 184" refId="B11" refString="Eberhardt, U, Beker, HJ, Schuetz, N, Pedersen, OS, Sysouphanthong, P, Laessoe, T, 2020. Adventurous cuisine in Laos: Hebeloma parvisporum, a new species in Hebeloma section Porphyrospora. Mycologia 112 (1): 172 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2019.1680220" title="Adventurous cuisine in Laos: Hebeloma parvisporum, a new species in Hebeloma section Porphyrospora." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2019.1680220" volume="112" year="2020">Eberhardt et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Good descriptions and further illustrations of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. lactariolens" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lactariolens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. lactariolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Corner, EJH" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" publicationUrl="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" refId="B8" refString="Corner, EJH, 1994 [&quot;1993&quot;]. Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337-357. https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" title="Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337 - 357." url="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" year="1994 [&quot; 1993 &quot;]">
Corner (1994 [
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1993”">&quot;1993&quot;</normalizedToken>
])
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" author="Clemencon, H" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="21 - 27" refId="B7" refString="Clemencon, H, Hongo, T, 1994. Notes on three Japanese Agaricales. Mycoscience 35: 21 - 27, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" title="Notes on three Japanese Agaricales." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02268524" volume="35" year="1994">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Clémençon">Clemencon</normalizedToken>
and Hongo (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
. Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Microscopic features of Hebeloma lactariolens (E 00204780); intended holotype of Psathyrella verrucispora nom. inval.) A spores in Melzer's reagent x 1600 B spore ornamentation in Melzer's reagent x 1600 C basidium in KOH x 1000 D cheilocystidia in KOH x 1000 E, F pleurocystidium in KOH x 1000 G caulocystidia in KOH x 500 H sectional view of cutis below the gelatinous epicutis in KOH x 500 I sectional view of ixocutis showing thin gelatinous epicutis in KOH x 125. Scale bars: 10 µm (A-H), 100 µm (I). Photographs H. J. Beker. J Exsiccata (a section of photograph from http: // data. rbge. org. uk / herb / E 00204780 provided by the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.77.57394.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502275" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">6</figureCitation>
, shows various macro and micro characters of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Corner’s">Corner's</normalizedToken>
intended type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corner" authorityYear="1993" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Psathyrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Psathyrella verrucispora" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="verrucispora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Psathyrella verrucispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
This species is rather variable molecularly and in the ML reconstruction forms a clade together with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. youngii" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="youngii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. youngii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an Australian species growing with 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eucalyptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eucalyptus" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Eucalyptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Corymbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Corymbia" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Corymbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to our knowledge only known from the type locality (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/12-404" author="Rees, BJ" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="1043 - 1058" refId="B36" refString="Rees, BJ, Midgley, DJ, Marchant, A, Lerkins, A, Orlovich, DA, 2013. Morphological and molecular data for Australian Hebeloma species do not support the generic status of Anamika. Mycologia 105: 1043 - 1058, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/12-404" title="Morphological and molecular data for Australian Hebeloma species do not support the generic status of Anamika." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/12-404" volume="105" year="2013">Rees et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Even though the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. lactariolens" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lactariolens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. lactariolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in relation to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. youngii" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="youngii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. youngii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not bootstrap-supported within this analysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. ML topology of concatenated ITS and MCM 7 sequences of Hebeloma and Alnicola. Flammula alnicola is used for rooting purposes. Bootstrap support based on 500 replicates and posterior probabilities based on a BI analysis are indicated at the branches. Assignment of species to sections follows Beker et al. (2016). Sequences in red are from Malaysian collections discussed in this paper. T indicates type collections. Thick branches indicate full support. AS - Asia, EU - Europe, NA - North America, O - Oceania, gr. - group." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.77.57394.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502270" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">1</figureCitation>
), although it is in the BI results (see TreeBase), the molecular distance, the occurrence on different continents, the different host associations, and morphologically, the cheilocystidia which for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. youngii" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="youngii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. youngii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more consistently lanceolate and the number of full length lamellae which for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. youngii" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="youngii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. youngii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the range 50-60 while for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. lactariolens" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lactariolens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. lactariolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is always less than 40, clearly separate these taxa. The Malaysian and Singapore records are from lowland tropical forests while the type has been described from a subtropical habitat from Japan, thus hinting at a wide climatic and geographical range. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. J. Rees &amp; Orlovich, Mycologia 105: 1055" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Clemencon &amp; Hongo" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma lactariolens" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lactariolens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Hebeloma lactariolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is according to observations of S. S. L. not uncommon in Malaysia. The FRIM database includes additional records of this species (not studied) from Hutan Simpan Semangkuk, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fraser’s">Fraser's</normalizedToken>
Hill, Pahang and the Pasoh Forest Reserve, Negeri Sembilan, from hill respective lowland dipterocarp forests.
</paragraph>
